**b.** Operation leverage can be measured using the degree of operating leverage (DOL). We can recall that the percentage change in operating cash flow and degree of operating leverage are related using this formula, assuming that taxes are negligible:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{DOL}&=1+\dfrac{\text{FC}}{\text{OCF}}
\end{aligned}$$

Where,

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{DOL}&=\text{Degree of Operating Leverage}\\
\text{FC}&=\text{Fixed Costs}\\
\text{OCF}&=\text{Operating Cashflow}
\end{aligned}$$
